        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1570327508" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15029546951490888694">Have you ever wanted something you know you absolutely should not want or have? Yet, you just cannot stop that little voice in your head and your heart from wanting it? Stone is an intense story of poverty, loss, strength and unwavering love. A love that is so strong it quite possibly might ruin everyone involved. <br/>If you are familiar with Angel Rose’s novels you know that Angel Rose will not lead you on the straight and narrow. You will be led down into a rabbit hole of lies, murder, and sin. Tr</span>
  <span id="freeText15029546951490888694" style="display:none">Have you ever wanted something you know you absolutely should not want or have? Yet, you just cannot stop that little voice in your head and your heart from wanting it? Stone is an intense story of poverty, loss, strength and unwavering love. A love that is so strong it quite possibly might ruin everyone involved. <br />If you are familiar with Angel Rose’s novels you know that Angel Rose will not lead you on the straight and narrow. You will be led down into a rabbit hole of lies, murder, and sin. Try as you might to figure out which way is up and out and who the bad guys are you won’t be able to. <br />Maddie is a great character, a child really in a woman’s role. Having to grow up way too fast in a cruel world surrounded by everything a child should never be around. Her world changed when Stone entered her shabby little trailer. He was a child himself, learning to be a man and a protector. He too has had to be the man of the house, never being a carefree boy.<br />Instead of your typical boy meets girl (love those too) love story, you get a dark and gritty forbidden love story. One that at the end of the day might kill both of them. <br />This is a series, I knew there would be a cliff hanger, but, DAMN Angel Rose…. She leaves you hanging on my one single figure on the edge of a cliff here. Humf! I am still pouting! Waiting for book two…. <br /></span>
