<span id="freeTextContainer7114582917618701583">Angel Rose knows dark romance. Those things you pretend don&apos;t exist. The worlds you shy away from. Horrible things people do to each other. She unveils these places through her characters eyes. Real people attempting to get by in their short dance upon the earth the only way they can. Angel shows us that even in dark reality, love exists. It pulls the characters together and makes their lives worth living. Romance is the potion which supports Mrs. Roses&apos; characters. It grants them the will to li</span>
  <span id="freeText7114582917618701583" style="display:none">Angel Rose knows dark romance. Those things you pretend don't exist. The worlds you shy away from. Horrible things people do to each other. She unveils these places through her characters eyes. Real people attempting to get by in their short dance upon the earth the only way they can. Angel shows us that even in dark reality, love exists. It pulls the characters together and makes their lives worth living. Romance is the potion which supports Mrs. Roses' characters. It grants them the will to live and keeps them going. In a word, Stone is beautiful. It will make you cringe, cry and gasp in a single sitting. You're emotions will become so confused all you will be able to do is turn the pages. You won't be able to stop. Five stars from me. A word of caution, Stone ends in a cliff hanger. Fortunately part two, Saving Madison, just came out. I know what I am reading tonight. </span>
