<span id="freeTextContainer8303398745363084476">Joseph &quot;Tiny&quot; Shelton is the son of a drug addict and was dropped off in a trailer park when he was 14 years old. When he is sent to prison for murder he reinvents himself as Stone and longs to be back with Madison Stone and her kids.<br/><br/>Madison is in over her head. She is trying to raise 3 kids on her own and has a boss named Andrew Turner who is trying to control her and wants her for himself and will stop at nothing to have her. <br/><br/>Unfortunately there are unresolved feelings between Stone and Madiso</span>
  <span id="freeText8303398745363084476" style="display:none">Joseph "Tiny" Shelton is the son of a drug addict and was dropped off in a trailer park when he was 14 years old. When he is sent to prison for murder he reinvents himself as Stone and longs to be back with Madison Stone and her kids.<br /><br />Madison is in over her head. She is trying to raise 3 kids on her own and has a boss named Andrew Turner who is trying to control her and wants her for himself and will stop at nothing to have her. <br /><br />Unfortunately there are unresolved feelings between Stone and Madison and both of them do not want to give in to a forbidden love but neither want the other with anyone else. As Stone and Madison face more heartbreak what will they do to hold onto their family?<br /><br />This was such a beautiful yet heartbreaking book that had me so mad at the situation that Stone and Madison were in.<br /><br />So it took me a little bit to properly sort out the family dynamics but then everything clicked into place. I felt so bad for Madison with what she had to do to keep her family together and what Stone sacrificed for it all as well. <br /><br />I absolutely hate Andrew and I hated what he did to Madison and am so worried about what is to come with everything there. I can't believe the things that he did, especially to Daniel and Clarissa.<br /><br />It was also frustrating me that Stone could not get the answers he needed to figure everything out. I know that would make things much easier but I was still super frustrated!<br /><br />I am definitely scared about what is to come and I hope Stone and Madison are able to keep everything together! </span>
