        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1999213907" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12129774494592407159">Maddie is in trouble. She&apos;s eighteen, coming out of a broken and abusive home trying to raise her three younger siblings. Her drug-addict mother is dead, her grandmother isn&apos;t much better. The only person she can count on is Stone.<br/><br/>And he&apos;s in prison, maybe for the rest of his life.<br/><br/>Stone can&apos;t wait to get out of prison and see Maddie. He yearns to see her, even through their love is forbidden. When he finally gets out, nothing is the same. She has a job and a boss. A boss that she has to please, </span>
  <span id="freeText12129774494592407159" style="display:none">Maddie is in trouble. She's eighteen, coming out of a broken and abusive home trying to raise her three younger siblings. Her drug-addict mother is dead, her grandmother isn't much better. The only person she can count on is Stone.<br /><br />And he's in prison, maybe for the rest of his life.<br /><br />Stone can't wait to get out of prison and see Maddie. He yearns to see her, even through their love is forbidden. When he finally gets out, nothing is the same. She has a job and a boss. A boss that she has to please, a man that wants everything from her. The man who will take her away from Stone forever.<br /><br />Stone is a dark and taboo romance. Stone and Maddie love each other, but can't be with each other. They might be related, but they might not be. They come from horrible homes, their lives are terrible, but they have each other. Angel Rose does an amazing job of weaving in their tale of two people trying to escape poverty, violence, and drug addiction of their family, to make something better.<br /><br />But their past haunts them. And if Maddie doesn't please her boss, they'll loose everything. Stone is a dark tale, tragic, haunting, and harrowing. Angel Rose leads you through the black depths of the human soul in the first of her Forbidden Love series.<br /><br />If you're fan of romance with a dark bent, of stories that don't shy away from brutal realities, then this is a compelling story you won't be able to put down.</span>
