<span id="freeTextContainer13880561710487310798">I have had this book, well series actually, for awhile now but just have not had much of a chance to read anything other than ARC&apos;s or proofread different books for authors but I am now taking that time because I promised to read and review these books. I went into this book completely blind. I didn&apos;t even read the synopsis before starting because when I read a book by an author that is new to me, that&apos;s how I like to do it. I don&apos;t want to know what the story is about and I don&apos;t want anyone te</span>
  <span id="freeText13880561710487310798" style="display:none">I have had this book, well series actually, for awhile now but just have not had much of a chance to read anything other than ARC's or proofread different books for authors but I am now taking that time because I promised to read and review these books. I went into this book completely blind. I didn't even read the synopsis before starting because when I read a book by an author that is new to me, that's how I like to do it. I don't want to know what the story is about and I don't want anyone telling me what the authors writing style is. I like finding all of those things out on my own! This is not a book for people that have issues or triggers with abuse or violence, but it is a part of the story line. One thing I need to touch on is I would have really like more back-story on Stone/Tiny at the very beginning of the book. I kind of feel like I am missing out on some things that could have been told at the beginning, but that may definitely change because this is book is part of a series and I am soooo glad that the other books are already released and that I have them to read! Otherwise I might not be a happy camper because I do not like having to wait for the next book to release before I can read it especially if the first book ends with a bit of a cliffhanger. So I am definitely looking for ward to reading book 2 and book 3. </span>
