          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/41131030-stone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3429309831" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5765152604259834359">Stone meets Maddie when he&apos;s dropped off at her home by his father who claims his mother lives there. Stone grows up with Maddie not know if she&apos;s really his sister.<br/><br/>Now that they&apos;re both adults, the attraction between them is growing. Stone is a trouble man, who spends time in prison after committing a crime during his teen years. Maddie is struggling to take care of herself along with her younger siblings Bryan, Daniel, and Alyssa.<br/><br/>Maddie works for a man named Andrew, who is also her boyfriend. </span>
  <span id="freeText5765152604259834359" style="display:none">Stone meets Maddie when he's dropped off at her home by his father who claims his mother lives there. Stone grows up with Maddie not know if she's really his sister.<br /><br />Now that they're both adults, the attraction between them is growing. Stone is a trouble man, who spends time in prison after committing a crime during his teen years. Maddie is struggling to take care of herself along with her younger siblings Bryan, Daniel, and Alyssa.<br /><br />Maddie works for a man named Andrew, who is also her boyfriend. Andrew can provide Maddie with a good life, however he wants her to give up Stone and the kids or else he'll make her suffer. Andrew is a vile person and the scenes with him abusing Maddie was too much.<br /><br />As for Stone, even though he and Maddie don't know for certain if they're related, the two are in love with each other. But they never act on their feelings.<br /><br />The possibility that Stone and Maddie are brothe and sister was a huge ick factor. Also, there was no chemistry between them. Stone says he wants to protect Maddie and would do anything for her, yet he's got a hothead who constantly gets in trouble.<br /><br />I had high hopes for this book, but there were a number of factors that threw me off.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5765152604259834359" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

