        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2499073645" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12714836610727927090">Well this book is certainly not for the faint at heart. This isn&apos;t a pretty love story about a brother and sister it&apos;s so much more and so much worse. First off they aren&apos;t even sure their related. I mean with drugged out parents, a whore for a mother neither of them know for sure. I mean come on his father was stoned when he dumped him and he didn&apos;t even know who&apos;s house his father dropped him at. This story is filled with crap no one should go through and consequences of bad decision made out </span>
  <span id="freeText12714836610727927090" style="display:none">Well this book is certainly not for the faint at heart. This isn't a pretty love story about a brother and sister it's so much more and so much worse. First off they aren't even sure their related. I mean with drugged out parents, a whore for a mother neither of them know for sure. I mean come on his father was stoned when he dumped him and he didn't even know who's house his father dropped him at. This story is filled with crap no one should go through and consequences of bad decision made out of desperation. Like I said it's not a pretty story and sadly it's not a standalone. <br /><br />Anyway I know it being a series and not a standalone is a no no for some of you, but I gotta say if you're of a mind for a dark read this has all the elements to be a great series. I have read this author before and no I wasn't a fan. This time however I have to say I am enjoying this series more and will be looking into the next book in the series.</span>
