<div id="review_2882103467" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2882103467" />
    <a title="Linda Lee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70523524-linda-lee"><img alt="Linda Lee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547188583p2/70523524.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2882103467?book_show_action=true">Jul 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Lee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Lee" href="/user/show/70523524-linda-lee">Linda Lee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/41131030-stone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2882103467" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9310250849311274525">First time reader of Angel Rose’s. This book had quite a good storyline, but I thought it was poorly executed. It felt a bit jumpy and timelines didn’t match up. The characters were a bit wishy washy and didn’t flow naturally. However, with a good beta team and some editing, it could of made this a much better read. <br/>It’s a taboo trope stepbrother and stepsister, which isn’t for everyone and it may or may not be incest. It wholly depends on bloodlines, so don’t rush into feeling sickened. It’s ob</span>
  <span id="freeText9310250849311274525" style="display:none">First time reader of Angel Rose’s. This book had quite a good storyline, but I thought it was poorly executed. It felt a bit jumpy and timelines didn’t match up. The characters were a bit wishy washy and didn’t flow naturally. However, with a good beta team and some editing, it could of made this a much better read. <br />It’s a taboo trope stepbrother and stepsister, which isn’t for everyone and it may or may not be incest. It wholly depends on bloodlines, so don’t rush into feeling sickened. It’s obvious that Stone and Maddie have the same intense emotions, but they are fighting them for those very reasons. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9310250849311274525" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
